<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">#basic integral term in surplus function (epsilon denoted by x) - note that it is commented out.
#x3b:=subs(x3k1,x3k2,(u(mi[i],vi[i])*simplify(int(D[1](F)(x,i),x=0..k1)))-(u(ma[i],va[i])*simplify(int(D[1](F)(x,i),x=0..k2)))-((u(ma[i],beta[i]*va[i]))*simplify(int(D[1](F)(x,i),x=k2..k1)))-simplify(int(x*D[1](F)(x,i),x=k2..k1)));

#this piecewise is used instead of the integral above in case beta is estimated at &lt; 1, which implies that epsilon_Ak (k2) is &lt; 0
surp:=piecewise(k2&lt;=0,u(mi[i],vi[i])*simplify(int(D[1](F)(x,i),x=0..k1))-((u(ma[i],beta[i]*va[i]))*simplify(int(D[1](F)(x,i),x=0..k1)))-simplify(int(x*D[1](F)(x,i),x=0..k1)),(u(mi[i],vi[i])*simplify(int(D[1](F)(x,i),x=0..k1)))-(u(ma[i],va[i])*simplify(int(D[1](F)(x,i),x=0..k2)))-((u(ma[i],beta[i]*va[i]))*simplify(int(D[1](F)(x,i),x=k2..k1)))-simplify(int(x*D[1](F)(x,i),x=k2..k1))):

#x3b plugs the equations for the espilon thresholds into the integrands surplus function
#x3b1 is a vector of equations from x3b for each relative income class:
x3b:=subs(x3k1,x3k2,surp);


x3b1:=[eval('x3b')$'i'=1..N]:</Text-field>
</Input>
<Output>
